name: SpacecraftLifeSupportTelemetry
title: Spacecraft Life Support Telemetry
description: A logical model representing Environmental Control and Life Support Systems (ECLSS) parameters monitored in spacecraft habitat modules.
purpose: To standardize telemetry data for environmental monitoring of spacecraft habitat conditions

element.definition: Oxygen concentration in cabin air, typically around 21%. Crucial for breathing; must stay in safe range to avoid hypoxia or fire risk.
element.comment: Target is approximately 21%. Alert if below 19.5% (hypoxia risk) or above 23% (fire hazard).

element.definition: Carbon dioxide concentration in cabin air, measured in parts per million (ppm).
element.comment: Kept low (thousands of ppm) to prevent crew headaches, dizziness. Alerts if above allowable limit (NASA 3 mmHg â 4000 ppm 1-hr).

element.definition: Nitrogen concentration in cabin air, typically around 78%.
element.comment: Primary buffer gas to maintain pressure. Changes may indicate pressure adjustments.

element.definition: Methane concentration in cabin air, measured in parts per million (ppm).
element.comment: Typically near 0. Monitored as part of atmospheric quality and as a flammability indicator.

element.definition: Hydrogen concentration in cabin air, measured in parts per million (ppm).
element.comment: Should be approximately 0; any reading flags a leak or issue as hydrogen is flammable.

element.definition: Water vapor partial pressure in cabin air, indicating absolute humidity.
element.comment: Managed to prevent condensation; relates to approximately 40-60% relative humidity comfort range.

element.short: Cabin pressure, temperature and humidity parameters
element.definition: Cabin pressure, temperature and humidity parameters

element.definition: Current ionizing radiation dose rate in the cabin.
element.comment: Reflects cosmic ray/solar radiation environment; used to assess immediate radiation risk.

element.definition: Cumulative radiation dose received during the mission.
element.comment: Tracks long-term exposure against established limits.

element.definition: Indicates if radiation has crossed thresholds requiring crew action.
element.comment: Values may include: 'nominal', 'elevated', 'storm'.

element.definition: Current shielding configuration of the habitat.
element.comment: Indicates if extra precautions are in effect due to radiation, such as 'standard', 'storm_shelter'.

element.definition: Percentage of radiation being attenuated by the spacecraft structure.
element.comment: Optional metric that indicates how much radiation is being blocked.

element.definition: The date and time when the environmental measurements were recorded.
Reference to the specific module or compartment where these measurements were taken.
element.comment: Important for spacecraft with multiple habitable volumes that may have different environmental parameters.

element.definition: Reference to the spacecraft or habitat module where these measurements were taken.
